			<item>
				<title>my hardware</title>
				<link>/personal/hardware/</link>
				<pubDate>Mon, 13 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
				<guid>/personal/hardware/</guid>
				<description>&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;macbook air&lt;/strong&gt;, m1 / 16gb / 512gb - allows me the freedom of taking all the work i do at home everywhere i want to. my main &amp;ldquo;&amp;ldquo;&amp;ldquo;desktop&amp;rdquo;&amp;rdquo;&amp;rdquo; at home.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;desktop&lt;/strong&gt;. ryzen 3 3100, gtx 1660 super, teamgroup vulcan z 32gb ddr4 @ 3600mhz, 1tb crucial t500, 1tb crucial mx500, 1tb wd caviar blue (from 2013). gigabyte b550m-k. antec truepower 750w from like 2013 (cause the one i had in it broke horribly). montech air 903 max (&lt;strong&gt;would recommend!!&lt;/strong&gt;). mostly just there to host files for me and sometimes stream vr sessions to my quest 3.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;lg ultrafine 32&amp;quot; 4k 144hz monitor&lt;/strong&gt; - it&amp;rsquo;s overkill for my lower-midrange pc desktop but it was a good deal. i still feel weird about having it, but no one wants to buy it. oh well.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;audio technica ath-m50x&lt;/strong&gt; - very stimulating headphones. not the most comfortable out there. the hinge broke so i had to glue it back together, now it sits lopsided.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;</description>
			</item>
